# Frontend Architecture Rules

## 1. Architectural Style
Frontend must follow a feature-based, component-driven architecture.

---

## 2. Layer Responsibilities

### Pages (Route Layer)
- Pages compose features and components
- Pages must NOT contain business logic
- Pages must NOT perform direct API calls

---

### Components (UI Layer)
- Components are responsible for rendering UI
- Components must be small, reusable, and single-purpose
- Components must NOT contain data-fetching logic

---

### Services (Data Layer)
- All external communication must go through services
- Services are the ONLY layer allowed to call APIs
- Services must not contain UI logic

---

### State Layer
- State must be centralized per feature or domain
- Business state must be separated from UI state when possible

---

## 3. Data Flow Rule
Strict unidirectional flow:

API → Service → State → Component → UI

---

## 4. Separation of Concerns
- UI logic stays in components
- Data fetching stays in services
- State orchestration stays in state layer or hooks
- No cross-layer responsibilities allowed

---

## 5. Dependency Rule
- Components depend on services (never on raw APIs)
- Services depend on API adapters or clients
- UI must never depend on external data shape directly